Text:
The next day, Cid chases Delta through the
underground waterways.

(Hunting is Delta's specialty. The way she conceals
her presence is honestly impressive. She might be
the cream of the Seven Shadows' crop.)

(What's more, her ability to sense prey is off the
charts. To be honest, her sense of smell and hearing
are probably even better than mine.)

(With the notable exception of her brains, every
aspect of Delta's is top-of-the-line.)

(That's the reason I'm having her run ahead of me and
act as my Bandit Radar.)

(Going on bandit hunts with Delta isn't all sunshine
and rainbows. There are downsides too.)
Gyargh!
Aaaaaah.
(As a rule of thumb, Delta can't "stay.")

(Staying put in front of her prey seems to cause her
immense stress.)

(She'll behave herself as long as I'm around, but the
minute I'm gone, she'll have no choice but to vent
it. That invariably causes problems.)

(She might end up mounting Gamma to assert dominance,
or chop down all the trees behind someone's house and
leave the lot barren, or find a vegetable field and eat
everything in it...)

(Back when she was a kid, it stopped there... Now
that she's grown up, though, I have no idea how
destructive her stress-relieving methods might be.)
Gyargh!
Aaaaaah.

(Her hunting is a one-sided massacre, although it
does make treasure hunting easy.)
That said, where's the fun in a battle like that?
Wait! Please, wait!
Hm?
Has Delta stopped...? Impossible.
It's you, isn't it, Sara! Look, it's me! It's me!
It's me! Zabra! You remember me, don't you?! Sara!
Hm...? *sniff sniff*
You smell like Dad.
Yeah-yeah! It's your older brother! Zabra...!

But, Sara, how did you survive? I'd heard you
contracted the possession, and the old man
hunted you down...!

I'm the best at hide-and-seek, or my name isn't
Delta.

Del...ta? So that's what you call yourself these
days, huh?
A weakling is no brother of mine.
You sure? Wasn't that your brother?
Weaklings are a stain on the family name.
I...see.

My dad is a tribal chief! He has a ton of lovers and
over a thousand children!

Well, in that case, he can definitely stand to lose
one or two.

Weaklings die! If one dies, we birth more! That's the
tribal rule!

(That's therianthropes for you. They operate on crazy
scales.)
(There's the occasional intellectual therianthrope,)
Hm-hm-hmmm.

(but they're mostly a group who believes "might makes
right.")

You know, I kinda want to check out the therianthrope
lands at some point...
Ooh, good idea!
You can become chief, Boss man!
Huh?
You can beat up my dad and then become chief!

Then you can make lots of babies and become the
strongest family in the world!
That's definitely not on the agenda.
It is! We'll find you a hundred women!
I'll give birth to a hundred babies too!

Not happening. C'mon, the hunts over. We're heading
back.
Ha-ruff...
Zabra was killed?

Yes, one of our underground hideouts was attacked,
and we discovered bodies inside...

Um...Lord Gettan, our ranks have taken heavy losses
in recent months. If this continues, it will impact
our operations above ground...

We've poured considerable resources into establishing
the bank. And the bribes we've given the council
members to issue bills have been substantial...
Perhaps we should take a moment to regroup—
Garter.
Sir!

Your position overseeing the circulation of goods in
the kingdom... You haven't forgotten who you owe
that position to, have you?
No! Of course not, sir!
All you need to do is follow orders.
Our orders.
Ulp...
In any case, Zabra was the weakest of the Clovers.

Summon the remaining three. Intensify the attack on
Mitsugoshi and seize every one of their secrets.
U-Understood!

Garter practically flees the room in his hurry to
leave.

His job is to destroy Mitsugoshi. That's why he's
taken over the Garter Corporation.

Word came down from the Cult's top brass: Mitsugoshi
is growing faster than they'd predicted, and if they
keep expanding at this rate, there's a chance they'll
end up posing a problem.
Mitsugoshi is...surprisingly tenacious.

Perhaps that explains why the Cult sees them as a
threat.
